px solid transparent;border-style:solid solid none;border-width:15px 15px medium;width:0;margin-left:40px;"></div></div></div>\n<div class="yom-mod yom-art-branding"></div>\n<div class="yom-mod yom-art-hd"><div class="bd"><h1 class="headline">Falcao Leads Atletico, Sporting Win in Europa League: Fan Take</h1><a href="http://contributor.yahoo.com/" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/.23PAFLrlpIheXZDQy4SdA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9Zml0O2g9MzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/logo/associatedcontent/ycn_icon.png" alt="Yahoo! Contributor Network" title="" class="logo"></a><cite class="byline vcard"><div class="yom-art-author"><div class="bd"><div class="profile hidden"><div class="info clearfix"><p class="author-name">By <span class="fn"><a href="http://contributor.yahoo.com/user/3331/jeff_musall.html">Jeff Musall</a></span></p></div><div class="links"><ul class="clearfix"><li class="first"><a>Posts</a></li><li class="last"><a href="http://contributor.yahoo.com/user/3331/jeff_musall.html">Website</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div>By <span class="fn"><a href="http://contributor.yahoo.com/user/3331/jeff_musall.html">Jeff Musall</a></span> | <span class="provider org">Yahoo! Contributor Network</span>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<abbr title="2012-04-20T00:46:00Z">Thu, Apr 19, 2012 8:46 PM EDT</abbr></cite></div></div>\n<div class="yom-mod social-buttons"><div class="bd"><div id="ymsb-13370840061682-1" class="ymsb ymsb-facebook ymsb-retweet ymsb-inshare ymsb-googleplus ymsb-mail"></div></div></div>\n\n\n<!-- START article -->\n<div class="yog-wrap yom-art-bd">\n    <div class="yog-col yog-5u">\n\n<div id="yom-ad-SKY" class="yom-ad"><center><!-- SpaceID=0 robot -->\n</center></div>\n\n<!-- yog-5u --></div>\n    <div class="yog-col yog-11u"><?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Root></Root>\n<div class="yom-mod yom-art-content "><div class="bd"><p class="first">The Europa League semifinals took place April 19, and provided fans with two good games with standout performances. The contest is down to three Spanish teams and one from Portugal, with the second leg of the semifinals yet to be played. In the first leg,\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\n<b>Atletico win featured Falcao brace</b>\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\nClub Atletico de Madrid holds the upper hand in their semifinal with Valencia CF, thanks to a 4-2 win that set them up and favorites to advance to the Europa Cup final in Bucharest next month. Diego Simeone&#39;s side took the offensive early, making runs along the flank and bring in the ball for chances early and often.\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\nThe efforts <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2012/matches/round=2000276/match=2007476/postmatch/report/index.html#atletico+control+against+rivals+valencia">bore fruit in the 18th minute</a>, when Radamel Falcao found the back of the net for his 31st goal of the season. He followed it with a second in the 79th that seemed to make for a 4-1 win, until Valencia got their second stoppage time goal of the match.\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\nThe first goal in added time came as the intermission approached. Atletico were up 1-0 when Brazilian Jonas brought Valencia level. They were fortunate to enter the break with the score even, as Atletico were the better team of the first half. The even score couldn&#39;t hold very long in the second frame, as Jonas&#39; fellow Brazilian Miranda scored the go-ahead in the 49th minute.\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\nValencia would have been in an even deeper hole than they are if Ricardo Costa didn&#39;t get the other stoppage time goal at 90 minutes plus 4. The pressure on Valencia will only be lessened slightly by his score.\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\nMLS fans will get a chance to see Valencia CF in the United States in the summer. I will be seeing them play the Portland Timbers <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.portlandtimbers.com/schedule">at Jeld-Wen Field May 23</a>. The Spanish side will also be taking on the Houston Dynamo May 31.\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\n<b>Sporting earn late comeback win</b>\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\nSporting Clube de Portugal <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2012/matches/round=2000276/match=2007477/postmatch/report/index.html#capel+caps+sporting+comeback+against+athletic">were down a goal</a> entering the final 20 minutes of their semifinal against Athletic Bilbao until Emiliano Insua headed in the equalizer in the 76th minute. Just four minutes later, Diego Capel scored the winning goal. The Spaniard helped his side from Portugal take a step toward making sure the Europa Cup final isn&#39;t an all-Spanish affair.\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\nThey were the better side on the pitch, but Sporting&#39;s efforts looked like they might fall short until the last-20 heroics. When they go to Madrid for the second leg, Sporting will be quite thankful for the small cushion the 2-1 win gave them.\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\n<i>Jeff Musall is a lifelong fan of international soccer. He is fond of the competitions that seek to find the best side in a long competition like the Europa Cup or Champions League.</i>\n</p><p>\n</p><p>\n</p><p></p></div></div>\n\n<div class="yom-mod yom-follow" id="mediasocialfollow"><div class="bd"><div class="yom-iframe-wrap" id="mediasocialfollowtw-ifr" style="width:61px;height:22px;"><noscript><iframe src="http://platform.twitter.com/widgets/follow_button.html?screen_name=yahoosports&show_count=false&show_screen_name=false&width=61&height=22&lang=en" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" style="width:61px;height:22px;"> </iframe></noscript></div><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/user?region=screen_name&screen_name=yahoosports" onclick="window.open(this.href, &quot;share&quot;, &quot;width=550, height=450, scrollbars=no, menubar=no, resizable=no, location=yes, toolbar=no&quot;); return false;" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" title="Follow @yahoosports on Twitter">@yahoosports</a> on Twitter, become a fan on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/YahooSports" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Fa